WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.006 --> 00:00:07.841
["On Fire Again" playing]

2
00:00:07.924 --> 00:00:10.927
<i>♪ Oh. I'm on fire again ♪</i>

3
00:00:11.011 --> 00:00:12.929
<i>♪ In New York City ♪</i>

4
00:00:13.013 --> 00:00:14.347
<i>♪ Oh. yeah… ♪</i>

5
00:00:14.431 --> 00:00:16.349
[Kitty] <i>It's been three months</i>
<i>since I left Korea.</i>

6
00:00:16.433 --> 00:00:19.394
<i>and I've had the best summer ever</i>
<i>living in New York with--</i>

7
00:00:19.477 --> 00:00:22.147
[sighs] Kitty. this is weird.

8
00:00:22.230 --> 00:00:24.941
You're posing like you're having
some deep. introspective moment.

9
00:00:25.025 --> 00:00:26.484
- It--
- Just take the picture. LJ.

10
00:00:26.568 --> 00:00:28.778
I am choking on sewer steam out here.

11
00:00:28.862 --> 00:00:30.196
Okay.

12
00:00:30.280 --> 00:00:33.491
Wow. That's it. That's super natural.

13
00:00:33.575 --> 00:00:35.660
- That… Yeah. candid.
- Yep.

14
00:00:35.744 --> 00:00:36.995
That's… Wow.

15
00:00:37.078 --> 00:00:39.914
It's radiating. just. spontaneity.

16
00:00:40.749 --> 00:00:41.708
[sighs]

17
00:00:42.292 --> 00:00:44.377
[Lara Jean] Okay.
Let's check out this post.

18
00:00:44.461 --> 00:00:46.087
Wait. whose hand is that?

19
00:00:46.171 --> 00:00:48.965
Did you meet a girl at brunch
and not tell me?

20
00:00:49.049 --> 00:00:51.634
That may just be my other hand.

21
00:00:53.303 --> 00:00:56.765
Oh my God. Kitty.
You're catfishing Min Ho.

22
00:00:56.848 --> 00:01:00.435
- I am not!
- Yes! Yes. you are! [gasps]

23
00:01:01.186 --> 00:01:02.687
You've seen his Insta.

24
00:01:02.771 --> 00:01:05.315
He's partying
in a different city every other night.

25
00:01:05.398 --> 00:01:06.524
And we've barely talked.

26
00:01:06.608 --> 00:01:10.236
so I need to make sure he knows
my summer was equally as amazing as his.

27
00:01:10.320 --> 00:01:13.073
Even if it was spent
drying a lot of my tears?

28
00:01:13.156 --> 00:01:15.700
Whenever my sister needs me.
that is where I want to be.

29
00:01:16.534 --> 00:01:19.621
You're gonna figure this out with Peter.
I just know it.

30
00:01:19.704 --> 00:01:20.705
Maybe.

31
00:01:21.372 --> 00:01:24.751
I don't know. Our lives are just
not compatible right now.

32
00:01:25.502 --> 00:01:27.212
You know. with his job in California.

33
00:01:27.295 --> 00:01:30.548
and all… all the big publishing houses
are here in New York…

34
00:01:30.632 --> 00:01:34.552
Well. lucky for you. when you publish
your novel. you can write from anywhere.

35
00:01:34.636 --> 00:01:36.888
Those first three chapters? Page-turners.

36
00:01:37.514 --> 00:01:38.389
Kitty!

37
00:01:38.473 --> 00:01:41.851
If you did not want people reading it.
you shouldn't have put it in a drawer.

38
00:01:42.602 --> 00:01:45.772
Plus. I had to check if you were.
like. actually a good writer

39
00:01:45.855 --> 00:01:48.316
if I was gonna let you help me write
my NYU application essay.

40
00:01:48.399 --> 00:01:50.652
I told you
you were gonna like NYU. didn't I?

41
00:01:50.735 --> 00:01:52.112
- You were right.
- Mm-hmm.

42
00:01:52.195 --> 00:01:55.281
Just like how I'm right
about you and Peter.

43
00:01:55.365 --> 00:01:58.910
So if I go to NYU.
and you two make up and move in together.

44
00:01:58.993 --> 00:02:01.412
I will be over
every Sunday night for dinner.

45
00:02:01.496 --> 00:02:02.330
Fear not.

46
00:02:03.748 --> 00:02:05.834
On a scale of one to ten.
how much will you miss me?

47
00:02:05.917 --> 00:02:08.419
I feel like I'm gonna really love
having my personal space back.

48
00:02:08.503 --> 00:02:10.296
You wanna cuddle me at any given point!

49
00:02:10.380 --> 00:02:12.465
You stretched out my shoes
with your enormous feet.

50
00:02:12.549 --> 00:02:16.261
- I'm half a size bigger than you.
- Size and a half. at least.

51
00:02:20.348 --> 00:02:22.892
I am gonna miss you a 12. Kitty.

52
00:02:23.393 --> 00:02:26.646
Getting to watch you experience
all these new things

53
00:02:26.729 --> 00:02:29.607
and figure out
where you want to apply to college…

54
00:02:29.691 --> 00:02:33.862
I mean. like. that… that…
that is exactly what my heart needed.

55
00:02:33.945 --> 00:02:36.364
You know. whatever happens with Min Ho.

56
00:02:36.447 --> 00:02:41.077
I think it's important that you make sure
you take the time to discover who <i>you </i>are.

57
00:02:43.538 --> 00:02:45.790
Mm. Just make senior year count.

58
00:02:46.374 --> 00:02:47.375
I will.

59
00:02:48.585 --> 00:02:50.253
I can't believe I'm a senior.

60
00:02:50.837 --> 00:02:54.174
There's still so many things I wanna do
before my time at KISS is over.

61
00:02:54.257 --> 00:02:57.177
I know. And that is why I got you
a little going-away present.

62
00:02:57.260 --> 00:02:59.679
- I love presents!
- Yes. you do!

63
00:02:59.762 --> 00:03:01.347
- [chuckles]
- [Kitty sighs]

64
00:03:01.431 --> 00:03:02.515
[Lara Jean clears throat]

65
00:03:03.892 --> 00:03:06.644
{\an8}Regret nothing. remember everything.

66
00:03:09.189 --> 00:03:11.065
- Thank you. sister.
- Mm-hmm.

67
00:03:16.821 --> 00:03:18.031
[cell phone chimes]

68
00:03:22.410 --> 00:03:23.578
Yeah. you did.

69
00:03:23.661 --> 00:03:25.330
- ["Only One" playing]
<i>- ♪ Picture me ♪</i>

70
00:03:25.413 --> 00:03:27.582
<i>♪ Looking so cute like OMG ♪</i>

71
00:03:28.333 --> 00:03:30.168
<i>♪ Dreamin' 'bout ya ♪</i>

72
00:03:30.251 --> 00:03:32.587
<i>♪ Treasure. let's find out… ♪</i>

73
00:03:32.670 --> 00:03:35.548
[Kitty] LJ is right.
I need to make every moment count.

74
00:03:35.632 --> 00:03:38.468
So I'm calling it my Senior Sunset List.

75
00:03:38.551 --> 00:03:42.764
In Portland it's tradition for the seniors
to watch the sunrise on the first day.

76
00:03:42.847 --> 00:03:45.600
then gather again and watch the sunset
the night before graduation.

77
00:03:45.683 --> 00:03:49.479
So your Sunset List is everything
you want to do before the year is over?

78
00:03:49.562 --> 00:03:50.563
Oh. I love it!

79
00:03:50.647 --> 00:03:52.774
What do you have so far.
besides tomorrow's sunrise?

80
00:03:52.857 --> 00:03:54.067
Well. it's a work in progress.

81
00:03:54.150 --> 00:03:56.778
But figure out
where I want to apply to college.

82
00:03:56.861 --> 00:03:59.072
have a traditional Chuseok
with my Korean family.

83
00:03:59.155 --> 00:04:00.865
I was wondering if we would be on it.

84
00:04:00.949 --> 00:04:04.077
And I want to have a conversation
with Soon Ja fully in Korean.

85
00:04:04.160 --> 00:04:06.079
Crap. not Soon Ja. Imo-Halmoni.

86
00:04:06.162 --> 00:04:08.331
- Yes.
- We do not first name our elders here.

87
00:04:08.414 --> 00:04:12.418
Well. you can still call me Jiwon.
except when school is in session.

88
00:04:12.502 --> 00:04:16.256
I cannot believe you are actually
a teacher here now. And my RA.

89
00:04:16.339 --> 00:04:18.591
Does that make me like a nepo-cousin?

90
00:04:18.675 --> 00:04:20.301
Ha ha. Funny.

91
00:04:21.261 --> 00:04:24.347
Kitty. is it pathetic that I'm nervous?

92
00:04:25.306 --> 00:04:27.809
I don't know.
I've never even lived away from Halmoni.

93
00:04:27.892 --> 00:04:29.143
Please. you've got this.

94
00:04:29.227 --> 00:04:30.687
And I've got your back.

95
00:04:31.187 --> 00:04:32.605
[exhales slowly]

96
00:04:33.106 --> 00:04:34.607
- Thanks. Kitty.
- Mm.

97
00:04:34.691 --> 00:04:37.193
It's nice to know
we can lean on each other.

98
00:04:37.277 --> 00:04:39.153
I better go now
and review my lesson plans again.

99
00:04:39.237 --> 00:04:40.071
I'll see you later?

100
00:04:40.154 --> 00:04:43.366
<i>Annyeonghee-gah-seh-yo!</i>
Wait. no. <i>annyeonghee-geh-seh-yo.</i>

101
00:04:43.449 --> 00:04:46.077
You had it the first time.
Keep me updated on your list.

102
00:04:46.160 --> 00:04:48.621
[Kitty] <i>Which brings me to…</i>

103
00:04:49.122 --> 00:04:51.457
- [excited chatter]
- [gentle music playing]

104
00:04:54.585 --> 00:04:57.171
<i>…the most pressing item on my list.</i>

105
00:04:57.255 --> 00:05:01.759
<i>Ending the situationship</i>
<i>by defining the relationship.</i>

106
00:05:01.843 --> 00:05:05.263
<i>and lock it in with yet another</i>
<i>silver-screen worthy kiss.</i>

107
00:05:09.767 --> 00:05:10.601
Hi. Covey.

108
00:05:10.685 --> 00:05:14.022
I was starting to think that
we'd never be in the same time zone again.

109
00:05:14.105 --> 00:05:15.815
I can hardly believe it.

110
00:05:19.777 --> 00:05:21.988
I'm really looking forward
to hearing about your summer.

111
00:05:22.071 --> 00:05:24.699
I'm looking forward
to telling you about it.

112
00:05:24.782 --> 00:05:27.243
- [gentle music fades]
- [engine approaching]

113
00:05:29.037 --> 00:05:31.039
[tense rock music playing]

114
00:05:32.332 --> 00:05:36.044
- What a douche--
- Dude? I know that bike anywhere!

115
00:05:39.672 --> 00:05:40.673
Marius!

116
00:05:41.341 --> 00:05:43.092
[Kitty] <i>Okay.</i>
<i>I don't know who this guy is.</i>

117
00:05:43.176 --> 00:05:44.677
<i>but he totally just killed the vibe.</i>

118
00:05:44.761 --> 00:05:47.263
Bringing the drama from day one?

119
00:05:47.347 --> 00:05:49.515
I do love to make an entrance.

120
00:05:49.599 --> 00:05:50.516
I do.

121
00:05:50.600 --> 00:05:52.560
- [chuckles]
- Hi!

122
00:05:53.061 --> 00:05:54.520
Oh. Marius. this is Kitty.

123
00:05:54.604 --> 00:05:57.273
- [Kitty] Hi.
- Right! Dae's ex. The American.

124
00:05:57.357 --> 00:05:59.734
I remember you lot
would FaceTime for hours.

125
00:05:59.817 --> 00:06:02.362
Then you moved here.
Don't they call you the Seattle Stalker?

126
00:06:02.445 --> 00:06:04.072
- Oh. the Portland Stalker.
- Oh.

127
00:06:04.155 --> 00:06:07.283
Nobody calls me that… anymore.

128
00:06:07.367 --> 00:06:10.995
Well. it's nice to meet the girl who made
such an impression on my friend group.

129
00:06:12.038 --> 00:06:13.581
Anyways. Kitty and I were about to--

130
00:06:13.664 --> 00:06:15.833
I am dying to get the Four Horsemen
back together.

131
00:06:15.917 --> 00:06:17.794
It's senior year. baby.

132
00:06:17.877 --> 00:06:21.672
And I'm single now.
so we are gonna tear Seoul a new one.

133
00:06:21.756 --> 00:06:25.385
But first. I do need to take a shower.
so let me back into the suite. bro. Yeah?

134
00:06:25.468 --> 00:06:26.552
Please? Thanks.

135
00:06:26.636 --> 00:06:28.221
Sure. Yeah.

136
00:06:28.304 --> 00:06:29.597
Come with?

137
00:06:32.141 --> 00:06:33.434
Miss Covey!

138
00:06:33.518 --> 00:06:36.104
[Kitty] <i>What's a girl gotta do</i>
<i>to get one single. tiny.</i>

139
00:06:36.187 --> 00:06:38.606
<i>uninterrupted moment</i>
<i>of romance around here?</i>

140
00:06:39.315 --> 00:06:40.983
Hi. it's good to…

141
00:06:41.067 --> 00:06:43.444
Still not a hugger. I see. Copy.

142
00:06:43.528 --> 00:06:47.323
Thank you so much for having me back.
Professor. I'm so excited for senior year.

143
00:06:47.407 --> 00:06:48.741
I have so many things planned.

144
00:06:48.825 --> 00:06:51.994
I hope they include focusing on academics
because for a senior.

145
00:06:52.078 --> 00:06:53.621
you are woefully behind.

146
00:06:53.704 --> 00:06:55.706
What? How? Classes haven't even started.

147
00:06:55.790 --> 00:06:58.418
As a one-year exchange student.
you had fewer requirements.

148
00:06:58.501 --> 00:07:02.463
But now. you'll also have to fulfill
our graduation requirements.

149
00:07:03.339 --> 00:07:06.426
But I am going to graduate. right?

150
00:07:07.552 --> 00:07:09.512
I suppose you can still catch up.

151
00:07:09.595 --> 00:07:13.141
You'll have to make up a few classes.
starting with a Korean culture elective.

152
00:07:13.224 --> 00:07:15.768
Registration starts tonight at midnight.
My advice?

153
00:07:15.852 --> 00:07:17.145
Be on time.

154
00:07:17.937 --> 00:07:19.564
The easy ones fill up fast.

155
00:07:22.150 --> 00:07:23.067
[sighs]

156
00:07:23.151 --> 00:07:28.531
So you kissed her and then went and spent
the summer with a bunch of hot girls?

157
00:07:28.614 --> 00:07:30.241
[chuckles] Okay. that was work.

158
00:07:30.324 --> 00:07:33.327
We lost the Yisoo deal. so from now on.
wherever Eunice goes. I go.

159
00:07:33.411 --> 00:07:36.873
Meanwhile. Kitty was posting
all summer from New York.

160
00:07:36.956 --> 00:07:38.082
With guys and girls.

161
00:07:38.166 --> 00:07:40.626
It sounds to me like you're single. then.

162
00:07:40.710 --> 00:07:43.963
Well. technically.
Kitty and I haven't exactly. um…

163
00:07:44.046 --> 00:07:44.964
Marius.

164
00:07:45.590 --> 00:07:47.175
'Sup. big Dae!

165
00:07:47.258 --> 00:07:51.179
- [exclaims]
- [grunts affectionately]

166
00:07:51.679 --> 00:07:52.638
Good to see you.

167
00:07:52.722 --> 00:07:53.764
[exclaims]

168
00:07:56.017 --> 00:07:57.018
- Marius.
- Q!

169
00:07:57.101 --> 00:07:58.060
[both chuckle]

170
00:08:00.396 --> 00:08:01.397
You look well.

171
00:08:01.481 --> 00:08:04.358
Yeah. likewise.
I mean. you… you've been working out?

172
00:08:04.442 --> 00:08:07.069
Ah. USC coaches go hard.

173
00:08:07.153 --> 00:08:10.364
but better I get used to it now
before I'm a freshman.

174
00:08:10.448 --> 00:08:12.909
- It's official?
- It's official. I'm in!

175
00:08:12.992 --> 00:08:15.119
I'm gonna be a Trojan! Fight on!

176
00:08:16.037 --> 00:08:17.079
- Congrats!
- Thank you!

177
00:08:17.163 --> 00:08:19.499
- That's great. mate.
- Lads. look at us.

178
00:08:19.582 --> 00:08:21.959
I mean. the band's all back together.

179
00:08:22.043 --> 00:08:23.211
What else have I missed?

180
00:08:23.294 --> 00:08:27.757
Because so far. I know that
Min Ho is in a committed relationship

181
00:08:28.382 --> 00:08:29.258
with his job.

182
00:08:29.342 --> 00:08:30.676
[group laughs]

183
00:08:30.760 --> 00:08:32.970
That's so funny. [chuckles awkwardly]

184
00:08:33.054 --> 00:08:35.223
- That's good.
- Anyone else?

185
00:08:36.224 --> 00:08:38.643
Uh. Jin and I are together
and super happy.

186
00:08:38.726 --> 00:08:40.436
Like. the happiest I've ever been.

187
00:08:41.020 --> 00:08:46.275
Great. Well. I'm excited to meet
my roomie's new boyfriend.

188
00:08:47.026 --> 00:08:49.946
Actually. Dae and I have discussed it.
and we're gonna be rooming together.

189
00:08:50.029 --> 00:08:51.864
so you don't have to worry about that.

190
00:08:51.948 --> 00:08:56.452
You know how cranky I get if I don't get
my beauty sleep. I need the west window.

191
00:08:56.536 --> 00:08:59.497
- Yeah. sure.
- [chuckles slightly. sighs]

192
00:09:00.206 --> 00:09:02.917
So what're we all doing
for tonight. then? For fun?

193
00:09:03.000 --> 00:09:04.126
[Kitty] Oh. I have an idea.

194
00:09:04.210 --> 00:09:07.713
We could all watch the sunrise
before senior year officially starts.

195
00:09:07.797 --> 00:09:09.131
[whimsical music playing]

196
00:09:11.801 --> 00:09:14.971
You know what?
That sounds really lovely. Covey.

197
00:09:18.057 --> 00:09:21.602
Yeah. but if we really want
to kick senior year off right.

198
00:09:21.686 --> 00:09:25.439
I think we should take over
the senior lounge and throw a rager.

199
00:09:26.107 --> 00:09:29.151
Yeah. I mean.
it's the faculty welcome party tonight.

200
00:09:29.235 --> 00:09:30.861
That means that all the teachers--

201
00:09:30.945 --> 00:09:33.447
All the teachers are gonna be
on the other side of campus.

202
00:09:33.531 --> 00:09:35.241
[both grunt enthusiastically]

203
00:09:35.324 --> 00:09:38.995
You know. you do know
how to throw a hell of a party. bruv.

204
00:09:39.078 --> 00:09:40.705
[both laugh]

205
00:09:42.456 --> 00:09:45.334
I mean. that is kind of perfect.

206
00:09:45.418 --> 00:09:47.003
I just said "kind of."

207
00:09:47.086 --> 00:09:49.880
And of course.
um. we'll do the sunrise too.

208
00:09:49.964 --> 00:09:52.383
Yeah. maybe. I mean…

209
00:09:53.175 --> 00:09:57.388
I'm not really a morning person.
but we… we could play it by ear. Mm.

210
00:09:59.000 --> 00:10:05.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

211
00:10:07.189 --> 00:10:09.942
[scoffs] Okay. Kitty. you're gonna
break the glass on your phone.

212
00:10:10.026 --> 00:10:12.028
I'm inviting everyone to Senior Sunrise.

213
00:10:12.111 --> 00:10:14.280
I don't care if Marius thinks it's lame.

214
00:10:14.363 --> 00:10:16.907
<i>He's </i>lame.
Bulldozing over my plans like that?

215
00:10:16.991 --> 00:10:19.368
- Yeah. Marius is all about Marius.
- [scoffs]

216
00:10:19.452 --> 00:10:22.663
Which would be fine
if Min Ho wasn't all about him too.

217
00:10:22.747 --> 00:10:25.207
I thought Min Ho would want
to define the relationship.

218
00:10:25.291 --> 00:10:28.419
but now he's all.
"You throw a hell of a party. bruv!"

219
00:10:28.502 --> 00:10:31.255
Listen. Marius is an acquired taste.

220
00:10:31.339 --> 00:10:33.716
Not that I've tasted him.
'cause I haven't. What?

221
00:10:33.799 --> 00:10:35.176
Spill.

222
00:10:37.720 --> 00:10:38.804
Fine.

223
00:10:39.805 --> 00:10:44.352
Marius and I used
to secretly hook up sophomore year.

224
00:10:44.435 --> 00:10:46.020
- When he had a girlfriend.
- [gasps]

225
00:10:46.103 --> 00:10:49.774
I know. I'm not proud of it.
And… and Jin doesn't know anything.

226
00:10:49.857 --> 00:10:52.109
And the two of us are actually
in a really great place

227
00:10:52.193 --> 00:10:53.778
since he visited me this summer in LA.

228
00:10:53.861 --> 00:10:56.822
- So please. please don't say anything.
- I will not.

229
00:10:56.906 --> 00:10:59.325
[sighs] But you cannot live with this man.

230
00:10:59.408 --> 00:11:01.243
Stand your ground
and tell him to switch rooms.

231
00:11:02.453 --> 00:11:03.412
I will.

232
00:11:03.496 --> 00:11:07.041
Good. And I'm gonna stand my ground
and get my damn sunrise.

233
00:11:07.124 --> 00:11:08.751
- [sighs]
- [cell phone chimes]

234
00:11:11.712 --> 00:11:13.130
[Kitty] <i>How could this happen?</i>

235
00:11:13.964 --> 00:11:17.259
You're not coming back to KISS
for our senior year?

236
00:11:18.636 --> 00:11:23.474
Kitty. I tried. okay? My mom and I
can barely afford this place.

237
00:11:24.058 --> 00:11:27.436
She found. what. like. five million won
from my dad's secret stash.

238
00:11:27.520 --> 00:11:31.273
and tuition is 20 million.
so public school it is.

239
00:11:34.443 --> 00:11:36.487
What if we sold a few things?

240
00:11:37.113 --> 00:11:38.114
My clothes?

241
00:11:40.533 --> 00:11:41.742
No!

242
00:11:42.243 --> 00:11:44.704
Kitty. this is all I have left
of my old life.

243
00:11:44.787 --> 00:11:47.665
That is not true.
You have me and all of your friends.

244
00:11:47.748 --> 00:11:49.750
This is just clothes. Who cares?

245
00:11:49.834 --> 00:11:51.836
Do you know me at all?

246
00:11:52.336 --> 00:11:55.047
Yisoo. Valentino. Chanel?

247
00:11:55.131 --> 00:11:58.592
Hello. if we sold this stuff.
we could make at least 15 million won.

248
00:11:58.676 --> 00:12:02.346
You could pay for the first semester.
We could even get you back in the dorms.

249
00:12:02.430 --> 00:12:04.223
There is an open bed in my suite.

250
00:12:04.807 --> 00:12:08.769
No. no. Okay. even if I wanted
to sell these clothes. which I don't…

251
00:12:09.520 --> 00:12:12.022
I'd have to make tuition
before school starts tomorrow.

252
00:12:12.106 --> 00:12:15.109
and it would take hours
to upload these online.

253
00:12:15.192 --> 00:12:17.111
Oh! Min Ho's annoying friend Marius

254
00:12:17.194 --> 00:12:19.113
is having a party tonight
in the senior lounge.

255
00:12:19.196 --> 00:12:21.741
Oh my God. his parties are legendary.

256
00:12:21.824 --> 00:12:24.368
Whatever. The point is.
we could have a Yuri sample sale.

257
00:12:24.452 --> 00:12:26.746
We'll make an Insta post.
Everyone will come.

258
00:12:27.329 --> 00:12:30.624
Yuri. It's either
your clothes or your friends.

259
00:12:34.170 --> 00:12:36.756
We're gonna do this.
We're gonna do it. It's gonna work.

260
00:12:43.596 --> 00:12:44.930
Uh. we need to talk.

261
00:12:46.891 --> 00:12:48.559
I need you to switch rooms with Dae.

262
00:12:48.642 --> 00:12:50.770
Yeah. I… I picked up on that.

263
00:12:50.853 --> 00:12:53.022
You know. you can just ask me directly.

264
00:12:53.105 --> 00:12:56.525
We are friends.
Or at least. I thought we were.

265
00:12:57.401 --> 00:12:58.402
You're right.

266
00:12:59.570 --> 00:13:01.322
Can you please switch rooms with Dae?

267
00:13:02.323 --> 00:13:03.574
See. was that so hard?

268
00:13:05.826 --> 00:13:08.662
But no. I'd rather live with you.

269
00:13:09.497 --> 00:13:12.750
I think we had a really good thing going.
don't you?

270
00:13:14.460 --> 00:13:16.629
Oh. is Jin the jealous type?

271
00:13:17.713 --> 00:13:19.340
There's nothing to be jealous of.

272
00:13:19.423 --> 00:13:20.841
Then what's the problem?

273
00:13:33.562 --> 00:13:36.023
[Kitty] Okay. Oh my God. Okay.

274
00:13:36.690 --> 00:13:38.317
Okay. [sighs]

275
00:13:38.901 --> 00:13:41.403
- Kitty! Wait up!
- [sighs]

276
00:13:41.487 --> 00:13:42.446
Okay. allow me.

277
00:13:44.657 --> 00:13:46.867
You don't have the upper body strength.

278
00:13:46.951 --> 00:13:49.662
- I've seen you try to open a jar.
- Ah. what a gentleman.

279
00:13:51.914 --> 00:13:54.333
So. from Instagram. it seems like

280
00:13:54.416 --> 00:13:57.795
you were having a pretty good time
living it up in Manhattan this summer.

281
00:13:57.878 --> 00:13:59.004
Yeah. I was.

282
00:13:59.088 --> 00:14:01.715
Seems like you had a good time
partying all over the world.

283
00:14:01.799 --> 00:14:03.717
Yeah. I did. but that was work.

284
00:14:03.801 --> 00:14:05.803
Well. seems like you have
quite the knack for it.

285
00:14:05.886 --> 00:14:06.762
[scoffs]

286
00:14:06.846 --> 00:14:11.016
But now that we're back.
there's other stuff to focus on.

287
00:14:11.100 --> 00:14:12.226
Yeah. tell me about it.

288
00:14:12.309 --> 00:14:14.645
Now I have to juggle
managing Eunice and school.

289
00:14:16.188 --> 00:14:20.442
Right. Well. at least
you're on track to graduate.

290
00:14:20.526 --> 00:14:23.445
I mean. did you know you have to take
a Korean culture elective?

291
00:14:23.529 --> 00:14:25.990
Yes. Covey. What do you think
the "K" in KISS stands for?

292
00:14:26.824 --> 00:14:28.909
It's a basic graduation requirement here.

293
00:14:28.993 --> 00:14:31.453
Take Korean Media.
You watch a bunch of Korean films.

294
00:14:31.537 --> 00:14:34.164
Marius and I took it freshman year.
An idiot could pass.

295
00:14:34.248 --> 00:14:38.252
- Mm. Sounds perfect for him.
- Just wait. Marius <i>will </i>grow on you.

296
00:14:38.335 --> 00:14:41.213
- Yeah. like a fungus.
- [chuckles]

297
00:14:41.297 --> 00:14:42.631
[upbeat pop music playing]

298
00:14:42.715 --> 00:14:44.133
[both exclaim]

299
00:14:47.261 --> 00:14:48.262
No.

300
00:14:48.345 --> 00:14:52.892
[all chanting] Chug! Chug! Chug!
Chug! Chug! Chug! Chug! Chug! Chug!

301
00:14:55.060 --> 00:14:56.770
- Oh!
- [laughs]

302
00:14:56.854 --> 00:14:58.522
[group cheering]

303
00:14:59.899 --> 00:15:01.483
<i>Fighting. </i>mate!

304
00:15:04.445 --> 00:15:06.071
[both chuckle]

305
00:15:06.155 --> 00:15:07.948
- Oh. I love a pop-up.
- Ooh.

306
00:15:08.032 --> 00:15:10.743
Yeah. it looks like
Yuri's greatest hits are here.

307
00:15:10.826 --> 00:15:12.786
Indeed. We have tonight
to make enough money

308
00:15:12.870 --> 00:15:15.164
so Yuri can pay for school
and live in the suite with us.

309
00:15:15.247 --> 00:15:17.708
When you say living with us. you mean <i>us</i>?

310
00:15:17.791 --> 00:15:19.460
Yes. if that's cool with you?

311
00:15:19.543 --> 00:15:23.297
I mean. assuming we make enough money.
We are about halfway there.

312
00:15:23.380 --> 00:15:26.425
- Can I get a friends-and-family discount?
- [both] No.

313
00:15:28.427 --> 00:15:30.763
[in Korean] Sorry
you had to resort to this.

314
00:15:30.846 --> 00:15:31.680
[Yuri] It's fine.

315
00:15:31.764 --> 00:15:33.891
[in English] It's just stuff.

316
00:15:34.558 --> 00:15:36.769
[gasps] How much for your boots?

317
00:15:36.852 --> 00:15:40.689
Oh! Absolutely not.
These are priceless. Not for sale.

318
00:15:40.773 --> 00:15:41.899
[grunts]

319
00:15:43.734 --> 00:15:45.361
Just stuff. huh?

320
00:15:45.444 --> 00:15:48.155
[in Korean] They're vintage Yisoo.

321
00:15:48.656 --> 00:15:52.368
When Juliana was sent away last year.
they honestly got me through it.

322
00:15:53.702 --> 00:15:56.997
[in English] Min Ho. let's do
our famous flaming shot. bro.

323
00:15:57.498 --> 00:16:00.834
Nah. nah. I'm not drinking tonight.
I've got a sunrise to catch. remember?

324
00:16:00.918 --> 00:16:04.588
But surely one shot
isn't gonna kill you. mate.

325
00:16:05.089 --> 00:16:07.633
Nah. I can't. I… I'm good.
Thanks. though. I'm good.

326
00:16:07.716 --> 00:16:10.761
- [all chanting] Shot. shot. shot. shot!
- No!

327
00:16:10.844 --> 00:16:14.556
Shot. shot. shot. shot. shot!

328
00:16:14.640 --> 00:16:15.891
- Okay.
- Yeah!

329
00:16:15.975 --> 00:16:21.981
[all chanting] Shot. shot. shot.
shot. shot. shot. shot. shot. shot!

330
00:16:22.064 --> 00:16:24.274
Shot. shot. shot!

331
00:16:24.358 --> 00:16:26.276
[group cheers]

332
00:16:29.196 --> 00:16:31.907
[Kitty] <i>Why is everyone obsessed</i>
<i>with this guy?</i>

333
00:16:34.243 --> 00:16:36.245
Did you confront the fungus
about moving out?

334
00:16:36.328 --> 00:16:37.162
[Q] Mm-hmm.

335
00:16:38.455 --> 00:16:42.334
I tried. okay?
But Marius was all charming and… wet.

336
00:16:43.335 --> 00:16:44.378
Never mind.

337
00:16:44.461 --> 00:16:47.715
Look. it's fine. Making a stink about it
is just gonna raise questions.

338
00:16:47.798 --> 00:16:49.925
and I don't need Marius
telling Jin about our history.

339
00:16:50.009 --> 00:16:53.721
But Jin loves you. Q. Just tell him.
Don't let this bully manipulate you.

340
00:16:53.804 --> 00:16:56.181
- Beat Marius at his own game.
- You're right.

341
00:16:56.265 --> 00:16:57.558
[Marius] Whoo!

342
00:16:57.641 --> 00:16:59.393
- It's just…
- I'm the greatest. mate.

343
00:16:59.476 --> 00:17:01.270
…I think he's my weakness.

344
00:17:01.353 --> 00:17:04.356
- Well. he's not mine. [scoffs]
- Kitty.

345
00:17:05.399 --> 00:17:07.359
Whoo!

346
00:17:07.443 --> 00:17:09.069
Still undefeated! Who's next?

347
00:17:09.153 --> 00:17:10.237
I am.

348
00:17:10.904 --> 00:17:12.906
Kathy. you play beer pong?

349
00:17:12.990 --> 00:17:15.451
I do. Care to make this interesting?

350
00:17:15.534 --> 00:17:19.413
If I win. you switch rooms
and leave Q alone once and for all.

351
00:17:22.875 --> 00:17:25.961
- Can we talk?
- Yeah. of course.

352
00:17:30.090 --> 00:17:33.802
I wasn't aware you were so concerned
with Q's living arrangement.

353
00:17:33.886 --> 00:17:37.556
Yeah. And if I win. no Senior Sunrise.

354
00:17:39.933 --> 00:17:42.269
Deal. Rack 'em up.

355
00:17:42.352 --> 00:17:44.354
[energetic dance music playing]

356
00:17:51.361 --> 00:17:54.031
Yeah. I… I don't know. I…

357
00:17:54.740 --> 00:17:57.201
I feel like I just need
to get this out in the open.

358
00:17:57.284 --> 00:18:02.039
Marius and I used to hook up.
and I'm sorry I didn't tell you sooner.

359
00:18:02.539 --> 00:18:06.502
I get it. I mean. Marius is a lot.
but I understand the appeal.

360
00:18:07.002 --> 00:18:08.545
- It's in the past. right?
- Totally.

361
00:18:08.629 --> 00:18:10.881
I'm with you now. and you are all I want.

362
00:18:16.637 --> 00:18:19.264
[energetic dance music swells]

363
00:18:31.860 --> 00:18:32.986
Come on. Come on.

364
00:18:37.491 --> 00:18:39.076
<i>♪ Don't stop. now ♪</i>

365
00:18:39.827 --> 00:18:41.120
<i>♪ Keep going ♪</i>

366
00:18:41.203 --> 00:18:42.496
<i>♪ Don't stop ♪</i>

367
00:18:43.247 --> 00:18:44.498
<i>♪ Now go ♪</i>

368
00:18:45.207 --> 00:18:46.416
<i>♪ Don't stop. now ♪</i>

369
00:18:47.000 --> 00:18:48.043
<i>♪ Keep going ♪</i>

370
00:18:48.752 --> 00:18:49.586
<i>♪ Don't stop ♪</i>

371
00:18:50.546 --> 00:18:51.380
<i>♪ Now go ♪</i>

372
00:18:52.422 --> 00:18:53.590
<i>♪ Don't stop. now ♪</i>

373
00:18:54.466 --> 00:18:55.926
<i>♪ Keep going ♪</i>

374
00:18:56.009 --> 00:18:57.010
<i>♪ Don't stop ♪</i>

375
00:18:58.095 --> 00:18:59.680
<i>- ♪ Now go ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Let's go ♪</i>

376
00:18:59.763 --> 00:19:02.141
[background sounds distort. fade]

377
00:19:08.021 --> 00:19:10.774
[crowd cheers]

378
00:19:10.858 --> 00:19:12.151
Your turn. Kathy.

379
00:19:13.068 --> 00:19:14.361
It's Kitty.

380
00:19:24.580 --> 00:19:26.707
Oh. I'm still 500.000 short.

381
00:19:26.790 --> 00:19:28.458
[Madison] Oh. I love this song!

382
00:19:33.881 --> 00:19:35.382
- [Yuri] Hey. Madison?
- What?

383
00:19:35.465 --> 00:19:36.633
You still want these boots?

384
00:19:37.718 --> 00:19:39.094
I thought they were priceless.

385
00:19:39.178 --> 00:19:42.890
They're yours for… 600 thou.

386
00:19:42.973 --> 00:19:44.266
I'll give you five.

387
00:19:45.517 --> 00:19:47.436
- Done.
- [giggles]

388
00:19:54.693 --> 00:19:56.028
[laughs] Yay!

389
00:19:59.948 --> 00:20:01.116
[sighs]

390
00:20:05.329 --> 00:20:06.580
<i>♪ Go ♪</i>

391
00:20:06.663 --> 00:20:07.915
<i>♪ Don't stop. now ♪</i>

392
00:20:08.415 --> 00:20:11.084
<i>♪ Keep going. don't stop ♪</i>

393
00:20:12.127 --> 00:20:13.545
<i>- ♪ Now go ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Let's go ♪</i>

394
00:20:17.049 --> 00:20:18.800
[Kitty exhales slowly]

395
00:20:18.884 --> 00:20:20.677
[Kitty] <i>This is it. Kitty.</i>

396
00:20:20.761 --> 00:20:23.180
<i>Senior year is riding on this.</i>

397
00:20:25.557 --> 00:20:26.767
- Kitty!
- [Kitty] <i>Oh shit.</i>

398
00:20:27.351 --> 00:20:29.102
[crowd exclaims]

399
00:20:29.811 --> 00:20:33.148
Good game. Kathy.
Senior Sunrise is canceled.

400
00:20:35.901 --> 00:20:37.402
Can't wait to sleep in.

401
00:20:41.907 --> 00:20:43.325
What the heck. Kitty?

402
00:20:43.408 --> 00:20:46.161
I saw your post about Yuri's sale.
and I thought I would swing by.

403
00:20:46.245 --> 00:20:49.081
but I didn't expect
underage drinking on campus.

404
00:20:49.164 --> 00:20:51.625
That is a serious offense.
and I need to report this.

405
00:20:51.708 --> 00:20:54.419
No. Jiwon. you can't.
I am begging you. I will owe you my life.

406
00:20:54.503 --> 00:20:59.174
You are asking me to put my job at risk.
Is that what you meant by having my back?

407
00:20:59.758 --> 00:21:02.427
No. You're right. I'm sorry.

408
00:21:04.304 --> 00:21:05.305
[sighs]

409
00:21:08.475 --> 00:21:11.228
I'll give you five minutes
before I march back here with Lee.

410
00:21:11.311 --> 00:21:15.148
but this is the first and last time
I ever bail you out.

411
00:21:15.232 --> 00:21:17.859
You don't get special treatment
because you're family. Understand?

412
00:21:17.943 --> 00:21:19.111
Yes.

413
00:21:19.194 --> 00:21:20.279
Thank you.

414
00:21:23.907 --> 00:21:26.743
Principal Lee is on his way!
We're about to get busted!

415
00:21:26.827 --> 00:21:28.453
What? How did he find out?

416
00:21:28.537 --> 00:21:29.579
[woman] We gotta go!

417
00:21:29.663 --> 00:21:32.374
My cousin's a teacher here.
She saw the post about the sale.

418
00:21:32.457 --> 00:21:36.044
- Oh. so basically you narc'd?
- All right. it was obviously an accident.

419
00:21:36.128 --> 00:21:37.713
We only have five minutes.

420
00:21:37.796 --> 00:21:39.798
[students clamoring]

421
00:21:42.217 --> 00:21:44.720
[somber music playing]

422
00:21:44.803 --> 00:21:46.930
[Min Ho] Kitty! Where are you going?

423
00:21:47.014 --> 00:21:49.349
To bed. It's been a crappy day.

424
00:21:49.433 --> 00:21:50.434
Wait!

425
00:21:51.560 --> 00:21:53.145
Where are you going? Talk to me.

426
00:21:54.688 --> 00:21:57.274
I came back to KISS
wanting to make the most of this year.

427
00:21:57.357 --> 00:22:00.652
I had a list of all the things
I wanna do before we all run out of time.

428
00:22:00.736 --> 00:22:04.281
But school hasn't even started.
and somehow everything's gone wrong.

429
00:22:04.364 --> 00:22:06.408
I'm behind all my classes.
Jiwon now hates me.

430
00:22:06.491 --> 00:22:09.745
Marius is edging me out of my friend group
and ruined my Senior Sunrise.

431
00:22:09.828 --> 00:22:12.039
- And you--
- [splutters] Me? What about me?

432
00:22:12.122 --> 00:22:15.167
For starters. you spent your whole summer
partying with girl groups.

433
00:22:15.250 --> 00:22:17.753
It didn't seem like
you were sitting around pining for me.

434
00:22:17.836 --> 00:22:20.839
And now that we're back.
you're all about partying with Marius.

435
00:22:20.922 --> 00:22:22.257
[scoffs] Marius is an old friend.

436
00:22:22.341 --> 00:22:24.634
He got caught up
in the excitement of being back.

437
00:22:24.718 --> 00:22:27.679
Maybe I did too. It's our senior year.

438
00:22:27.763 --> 00:22:30.557
Exactly! And time is already ticking away.

439
00:22:32.851 --> 00:22:34.144
You want to know the truth?

440
00:22:35.270 --> 00:22:39.149
I spent the summer replaying that kiss
on the beach over and over in my head.

441
00:22:39.232 --> 00:22:42.694
just dreaming of having
another cinematic kiss with you.

442
00:22:42.778 --> 00:22:46.114
I even put it on my stupid Sunset List.

443
00:22:46.198 --> 00:22:48.325
This is our last year together. Min Ho.

444
00:22:49.076 --> 00:22:53.663
So I guess I got caught up in thinking
maybe you and I could be something.

445
00:22:55.040 --> 00:22:56.458
I think that I was wrong.

446
00:22:58.085 --> 00:22:59.252
About everything.

447
00:23:02.381 --> 00:23:04.216
<i>- ♪ Call me ♪</i>
- I…

448
00:23:05.217 --> 00:23:08.387
<i>♪ Call me honey ♪</i>

449
00:23:09.179 --> 00:23:12.265
<i>♪ Give me something ♪</i>

450
00:23:12.974 --> 00:23:16.436
<i>♪ I can keep… ♪</i>

451
00:23:16.520 --> 00:23:19.356
[Kitty] <i>I made a list</i>
<i>of all my hopes for senior year.</i>

452
00:23:19.439 --> 00:23:22.526
<i>But so far. all I've got are regrets.</i>

453
00:23:22.609 --> 00:23:27.155
<i>And the biggest one is that Min Ho and I</i>
<i>are finally in the same time zone.</i>

454
00:23:27.239 --> 00:23:30.158
<i>but somehow oceans apart.</i>

455
00:23:31.410 --> 00:23:33.620
- [gloomy music cuts out]
- Registration!

456
00:23:33.703 --> 00:23:35.705
[tense music playing]

457
00:23:43.505 --> 00:23:45.424
No. No.

458
00:23:46.425 --> 00:23:49.344
No! All the classes are taken?

459
00:23:50.095 --> 00:23:52.222
Except Korean Lit.

460
00:23:54.099 --> 00:23:56.852
- [sighs]
- [Kitty] <i>When it rains. it pours.</i>

461
00:24:12.367 --> 00:24:13.493
[cell phone chiming]

462
00:24:20.709 --> 00:24:22.461
["wherever u r" playing]

463
00:24:24.004 --> 00:24:26.923
Come on.
Min Ho wants to show you something.

464
00:24:27.007 --> 00:24:28.341
What is going on?

465
00:24:28.425 --> 00:24:30.510
[excited chatter]

466
00:24:30.594 --> 00:24:33.889
- Hi!
- [laughs] Did she have any idea?

467
00:24:38.351 --> 00:24:40.020
<i>♪ Lookin' back on a Sunday ♪</i>

468
00:24:40.103 --> 00:24:41.771
<i>♪ Pictures from the past now ♪</i>

469
00:24:41.855 --> 00:24:43.940
<i>♪ Sittin' all in the basement… ♪</i>

470
00:24:44.024 --> 00:24:46.776
[Kitty] <i>He got me my Senior Sunrise.</i>

471
00:24:49.279 --> 00:24:50.906
